Description: animated emoji tray pet that reacts to your machine's vital signs
 meowtrics shows a small animated emoji in your system tray
 (StatusNotifierItem) that morphs based on live sensor readings: CPU, RAM,
 thermals, battery, disk, network, and more. On hover it gossips about your
 machine using a weighted message database.
 .
 The KDE Plasma 6 frontend gets a richer popup with prose messages and per
 sensor breakdowns. Other desktops (GNOME with AppIndicator, XFCE, Cinnamon,
 Budgie, MATE, LXQt, Sway+waybar, etc.) get the tray icon and tooltip via the
 StatusNotifierItem standard. Tiling-WM users can consume the daemon's JSON
 output as a waybar/polybar/i3blocks custom module.
 .
 The default install ships only Unicode emoji (rendered via the user's system
 emoji font); optional companion packs (blobcat, neocat, openmoji, fluentui,
 twemoji) are available as separate packages with their own licenses.
 .
